race.comment: Lots of these off forgive runs. GIOVANNA STAR (4) returned with a great run though when placing over 1100m and beaten just over a length. Second-up winner fitter again and looks hard to beat again. JADE DIVISION (3) is on the quick back-up after being used up early and fading out of it over the weekend at Dubbo. Has a good record at the trip and also this circuit. Drawn well and is worth another chance. Best figures right up to this. PATTERA (2) was great two back in tougher but then disappointed in the latest. Has good speed and off the inside will take catching. THE DEFIANT ONE (5) is a fairly honest type with solid recent form. Has the claim and a low draw and gets a chance. LOUD (9) was safely held fresh but fitter and aided by the claim. Can improve sharply.
